subsection.def:
EAC Regulations (選管會規例) means regulations made under section 7 of the
                Electoral Affairs Commission Ordinance (Cap.
                541);

Electoral Affairs Commission (選管會) means the Electoral Affairs Commission
                established by section 3 of the Electoral Affairs Commission Ordinance
                    (Cap. 541);

paragraph.content:
the area of which is coloured pink and edged red on the map that bears
                        the number specified in column 2 of Schedule 1 opposite that
                        name;

an identity card issued to a person under the Registration of Persons
                        Ordinance (Cap. 177);
                        or

in relation to an Indigenous Village, means a holder of the office of
                        indigenous inhabitant representative established for the Village under
                            section 6(1);

in relation to a Composite Indigenous Village, means a holder of the
                        office of indigenous inhabitant representative established for the Village
                        under section 6(2);

in relation to an Existing Village, means the office of resident
                        representative established for the Village under section
                        5(1);

in relation to an Indigenous Village, means the office of indigenous
                        inhabitant representative established for the Village under section
                            6(1);

in relation to a Composite Indigenous Village, means the office of
                        indigenous inhabitant representative established for the Village under
                            section 6(2);

subsection.def:
Resident Representative (居民代表), in relation to an Existing Village, means a
                holder of the office of resident representative established for the Village under
                    section 5(1);

Revising Officer (審裁官) means a person holding office as a Revising Officer under
                    section 53, and includes any person appointed to act in place of such
                an Officer when the Officer is absent or the office is vacant;

paragraph.content:
a marriage celebrated or contracted in accordance with the provisions
                        of the Marriage Ordinance (Cap. 181);
                        or

subsection.def:
inclement weather warning day (惡劣天氣警告日) means a working day on which a gale
                warning or a rainstorm warning is in force at any time during the ordinary business
                hours of the office of the Electoral Registration Officer;

subparagraph.content:
in Hong Kong or any other place, of an offence for which the person has
                        been sentenced to imprisonment, whether suspended or not, for a term
                        exceeding 3 months without the option of a fine;

if the identity document held by, or previously issued to, the person
                        is an identity card, informs the Electoral Registration Officer of the
                        identifying number of the identity card;

if the identity document held by the person is not an identity card,
                        provides the Electoral Registration Officer a copy of the identity
                        document.

paragraph.content:
on the making of a declaration under section 12 as to the
                    existence of a vacancy in the office of rural representative for the Rural
                    Area;

on the making of a declaration under section 29(2) that an
                    election for the Rural Area has failed, or has failed to the extent mentioned in
                        section 29(2)(b);

on the making of a declaration under section 30(1) that the
                    proceedings for an election for the Rural Area have been terminated;
                    and

is not disqualified from being nominated as a candidate at the election, or
                    from being elected as an Indigenous Inhabitant Representative for the Village,
                    by virtue of section 23 or any other law;

subparagraph.content:
in Hong Kong or any other place, of an offence for which the person has
                        been sentenced to imprisonment, whether suspended or not, for a term
                        exceeding 3 months without the option of a fine;

the period of 30 days beginning on the date of the publication of
                            the result of election under section 36 (publication
                                    date);

section.def:
amending Ordinance (《修訂條例》) means the Rural Representative Election
                Legislation (Amendment) Ordinance 2014 (5 of
                2014);

paragraph.content:
the Market Town known as “Cheung Chau” which is included in
                            Schedule 3A added by section 16 of the amending
                        Ordinance;
